    public interface ParseInput<T>
extends Input<T>
    extended version of Input that supports parsing a String represenatation of the input

      • parse

        default void parse(java.lang.String v)
            throws ParseException
        Set the value of the input by parsing a textual representation of the input. Normally this defaults to using parseValue(String) and Input.setValue(Object) but it can be overridden for example if the natural parse mechanism generates an Item in an item input.

        Throws:
